---
title: "create-component — Generic Orchestrator Flow"
---
%%{init: {'theme': 'neutral'}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    actor U as User
    participant S as Skill
    participant R as Registry
    participant F as Figma
    participant A as Adapter
    participant FS as FileSystem

    U->>S: /create-component <name> [figma-url]

    note over S: Step 0 — Pre-flight
    S->>S: TodoWrite — init all tasks pending
    S->>FS: read template + registry + analysis
    note over S: extract naming_conventions<br/>+ styling_system

    critical Figma token check
        S->>F: whoami
        F-->>S: authenticated
    option EC5 — token invalid
        S-->>U: stop — fix FIGMA_ACCESS_TOKEN
    end

    note over S: Phase 1 — Context (3 parallel)

    par Agent 1 — Figma design
        S->>F: get_design_context(nodeId, fileKey)
        F-->>S: layout + colors + typography
        S->>F: get_design_context(nodeId, disableCodeConnect)
        F-->>S: full structure + variants<br/>+ icon nodes list
    and Agent 2 — Reuse check
        S->>R: load registry
        R-->>S: known components
        note over R: EXACT / PARTIAL / NO match
    and Agent 3 — Token sync
        S->>FS: read token file
        S->>F: get_variable_defs(nodeId, fileKey)
        F-->>S: Figma variables
        note over S: compare by value<br/>matched / missing tokens
    end

    alt EXACT MATCH
        S-->>U: already exists — reusing
    else PARTIAL MATCH
        S-->>U: extend or refactor?
        U-->>S: choice
    else EC2 — on disk, not in registry
        S-->>U: overwrite / register / cancel?
        U-->>S: choice
    end

    opt EC3b — token name mismatch
        S-->>U: Figma name vs local name<br/>map or skip?
        U-->>S: mapping confirmed
    end

    opt EC11 — no Figma tokens
        S-->>U: generate empty / cancel?
        U-->>S: choice
    end

    opt Phase 1.5 — Composite detected
        note over S: Decompose bottom-up
        S->>S: build dependency tree<br/>(deepest children first)
        note over S: classify each child<br/>by FSD layer
        note over S: build children before parent
    end

    note over S: Phase 2 — Implement

    opt EC6 — special chars in name
        S-->>U: converted name preview
        U-->>S: confirm / edit
    end

    par Stream A — Download assets
        loop each icon node
            S->>F: fetch SVG (nodeId)
            F-->>FS: img/<kebab-name>.svg
        end
    and Stream B — Generate code
        S->>FS: add missing tokens to token file
        S->>A: generate(template, tokens,<br/>variants, layer, styling_system)
        note over A: adapter writes CSS + JS<br/>+ preview file
        A-->>FS: component files written
        S->>FS: register @import in main CSS
        S->>S: run component-done checklist
    end

    opt EC4 — no icons detected
        note over S: log note, continue
    end

    opt EC12 — child not in registry
        note over S: create as local<br/>non-blocking
    end

    opt EC7 — style wiring
        note over S: read styling_system<br/>from frontend-analysis.json
    end

    opt Phase 3 — Visual verify
        S->>A: visual_verify(component, figma_ref)
        note over A: adapter-specific<br/>(SSIM / screenshot / etc.)
        A-->>S: pass / fail + report
        note over S: on fail — adapter handles<br/>retries + escalation
    end

    note over S: Phase 4 — Registry
    S->>R: upsert(name, type, layer,<br/>path, figma_node_id, status)
    R-->>S: written

    note over S: Phase 5 — Code Connect
    S->>FS: scan for primitive<br/>(*.figma.ts / *.figma.js)

    alt EC13 — no primitive found
        S-->>U: no primitive detected<br/>run /create-primitive first
        U-->>S: primitive created
    end

    S->>FS: read primitive → extract CC pattern
    note over S: discovers format + template<br/>+ publish command

    S->>F: get_code_connect_map(nodeId, fileKey)
    F-->>S: existing mappings (if any)

    opt existing CC mapping
        S-->>U: show old → new — replace?
        U-->>S: confirmed
    end

    S->>FS: write <name>.figma.{ext}
    S->>A: cc_publish(--dry-run)
    A-->>S: validation ok
    S->>A: cc_publish
    A-->>S: published

    S-->>U: done — files + registry + Code Connect

    note over S,A: Tool Failure Pattern
    note over S: critical tool fails →<br/>stop + structured report
    note over S: non-critical tool fails →<br/>log in report, continue
